{"tid":1878067,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"專家指出新型冠狀病毒在低溫及潮濕環境存活更久","createTime":"2020-02-13T11:23:54.000Z","updateTime":"2020-02-13T12:43:12.000Z","uid":30791,"like":5,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":17,"replies":[{"pid":"7db044d4934b49a41b93ce5d7b03ed875066e997","tid":1878067,"uid":30791,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-13T11:23:54.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>Reviewing the literature on all available human and veterinary viruses within this family, encompassing 22 studies, researchers have found that the human pathogens can persist on surfaces and remain infectious at room temperature for up to nine days. (To put that in perspective, the measles virus can live on contaminated surfaces for up to two hours.)<br />\n<br />\nGranted, that's the upper end of a coronavirus lifespan, but on average, researchers say this family of viruses can survive between four and five days on various materials like aluminium, wood, paper, plastic and glass.<br />\n<br />\nSome of the veterinary coronaviruses - the ones that can only infect animals - could even persist for longer than 28 days.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Low temperature and high air humidity further increase their lifespan,&quot; says physician G&uuml;nter Kampf at the Greifswald University Hospital.<br />\n</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.sciencealert.com/study-shows-just-how-long-coronaviruses-can-stick-around-on-a-surface\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencealert.com%2Fstudy-shows-just-how-long-coronaviruses-can-stick-around-on-a-surface&d=3BA04jbrysekxL3Ytp5IvUWuH9aop70KQP2vpO%2BUA2I%3D&h=b972149a\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.sciencealert.com/study-shows-just-how-long-coronaviruses-can-stick-around-on-a-surface</a>"},{"pid":"054974ef2b47c6abad03b4b304780d557f3f763a","tid":1878067,"uid":195257,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-13T11:27:54.000Z","msg":"香港濕凍世界第一？<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" clas